description:
Add ntfy.zt virtual host to Caddy reverse proxy configuration.

Reference pattern in modules/machines/nixos/cinnabar/caddy.nix lines 18-27:

"clawdbot.zt" = {
  listenAddresses = [
    "fddb:4344:343b:14b9:399:93db:4344:343b"
    "10.147.17.1"
  ];
  extraConfig = '
    tls internal
    reverse_proxy [::1]:2586
  ';
};

Use port 2586 (ntfy-sh default). Same dual-stack listenAddresses as the existing virtual hosts. Port 443 on zt+ interfaces is already allowed by the existing firewall rule in caddy.nix line 32.

ntfy uses WebSocket for real-time subscriptions. Caddy handles WebSocket upgrade transparently via reverse_proxy, no special config needed.

Create modules/machines/nixos/cinnabar/ntfy.nix with the ntfy-sh NixOS module configuration.

This file will be auto-discovered by the import-tree pattern (same as matrix.nix, caddy.nix, zt-dns.nix).

Configuration:

{ ... }:
{
  flake.modules.nixos."machines/nixos/cinnabar" = {
    services.ntfy-sh = {
      enable = true;
      settings = {
        listen-http = "127.0.0.1:2586";
        base-url = "https://ntfy.zt";
      };
    };
  };
}

No auth needed -- ZeroTier provides the access boundary. No firewall rule needed for port 2586 since ntfy binds to localhost only and Caddy proxies via loopback.

The NixOS module is at nixos/modules/services/misc/ntfy-sh.nix in nixpkgs. It supports freeform YAML settings via services.ntfy-sh.settings.
